      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Pertains mainly to Robert Bolling (1646-1709) of England
         and Virginia and his descendants. Includes a genealogical
         chart, lists of slaves belonging to John Bolling in 1711 and
         Anne Bolling in 1709, and a document certifying the number of
         inhabitants in Charles City County in 1699. Other allied
         families mentioned include Rolfe and Stith.</p>
         <p>All of the items were handwritten in a copy of John Purvis'
         <emph render="italic">A Complete Collection of All the Laws of
         Virginia Now in Force</emph> (1682), housed in Special
         Collections at the Library of Virginia.</p>
      </scopecontent>
